 Playing optimally (Minimax): {R}

This strategy assumes that the anonymous player is also playing optimally and seeks to maximize their own earnings. The optimal move for a human player would be the one that guarantees the highest possible average payoff over the long run, which in this case is choosing 'R'. This is because if the opponent always chooses 'B', then the human player's average payoff over 75 rounds will be 42$. However, if the opponent sometimes switches to 'R', the human player can earn 45$ in those instances, significantly improving their average payoff.

On the other hand, if the anonymous player always picks 'R', the human player's best strategy is to pick 'B' for every round, earning an average of 12$. Since we don't know our opponent's exact strategy, playing optimally means choosing 'R' as it provides a higher potential payoff.
